  "title": "Computer Science Core Subjects",
  "content": "<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span>This guide is designed to help you learn core computer science subjects. It covers topics like Operating Systems, DBMS, Computer Networks, Programming, Data Structures, and more, offering detailed tutorials.</span></p><h3 id=\"1-computer-science-basics\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>1. Computer Science Core Foundations</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/computer-science-fundamentals/computer-fundamentals-tutorial/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Computer Fundamentals </span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/engineering-mathematics/engineering-mathematics-tutorials/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Engineering Mathematics</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/computer-science-fundamentals/mathematics-for-computer-science/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Maths for Computer Science</span></a></li></ul><h3 id=\"3-systems-operating-environments\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>2. Systems &amp; Networking</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/operating-systems/operating-systems/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Operating Systems</span></a><span> </span></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/computer-organization-architecture/computer-organization-and-architecture-tutorials/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Computer Organization and Architecture</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/computer-networks/computer-network-tutorials/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Computer Networks</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/theory-of-computation/theory-of-computation-automata-tutorials/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Theory of Computation</span></a></li><li value=\"5\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/compiler-design/compiler-design-tutorials/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Compiler Design</span></a></li><li value=\"6\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/distributed-systems/distributed-systems-tutorial/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Distributed Systems</span></a><span> </span></li><li value=\"7\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/linux-unix/linux-tutorial/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Linux Tutorial</span></a></li><li value=\"8\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/ethical-hacking/cyber-security-tutorial/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Cybersecurity Tutorial</span></a></li></ul><h3 id=\"4-data-and-database-technologies\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>3. Data and Database Technologies</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/dbms/dbms/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Database Management System (DBMS)</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/dbms/data-warehousing-tutorial/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Data Warehousing</span></a></li></ul><h3 id=\"5-data-science\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>4. Data Science</span></h3><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/machine-learning/machine-learning/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Machine Learning Tutorial</span></a><span> </span></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/artificial-intelligence/artificial-intelligence/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Artificial Intelligence Tutorial</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-analysis/data-analysis-tutorial/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Data Analysis Tutorial</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science-with-python-tutorial/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Data Science Tutorial</span></a></li></ul><h3 id=\"4-programming-software-development\" style=\"text-align:left\"